Youthful & Faithful: Local young priests describe their calling to serve God Middle school hero: Platteville boy lauded for saving family from fire Biz Buzz: Abandoned Millwork properties purchased, Dubuque optical company wins contest, new store in Galena Iowa briefs ( … ) Plan: Former school to turn into apartments 
DAVENPORT — The state has given preliminary approval to grants that will help finance the renovation of an architecturally significant former school in Davenport into senior-living apartments. 
Tina Hoffman, of the Iowa Economic Development Authority, said that a final decision is expected shortly. 
Developer Chris Ales said he has been told he will receive a $3 million grant from the authority to turn the former Buchanan Elementary School into 18 senior apartments. The federal funds have been made available to communities affected by flooding in 2008 and are designated for new housing projects. Public asked to help name new eaglets 
DAVENPORT — Three new eaglets in a nest at Arconic Davenport Works need names. 
Arconic, which supports an oft-viewed eagle webcam, is taking suggestions through Wednesday from the public for names. Arconic will narrow the list of suggestions and create an online poll for eagle-cam fans to vote. 
Those wanting to suggest names must visit and “like” the Arconic Davenport Works Facebook page. Name suggestions can be left in the comment section of the eaglet name post. Eagle-cam viewers also can tweet their name ideas using the hashtag #alcoaeaglecam or post a comment to the Eaglecam blog.
